<li id="cite_note-16"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Kirkpatrick Sale, <i>Dwellers in the Land: the Bioregional Vision,</i> University of Georgia Press, 2000, pp.153-4</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Jeff Lewis, <i>Cultural Studies: the Basics,</i> Sage Publications, 2008, p.106</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-18"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Sugata Bose &amp; Ayesha Jayal, <i>Modern South Asia: History, Culture, Political Economy,</i> Routledge, 2004, p.164 &amp; p.220</span>
</li>
</ol></div></div>
